<HEADLINE> Nasdaq, Dow Up in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mixed in early trading on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average is up a fraction in the early
going. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a slim
lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 60 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up more than a point.
</P>
<P>
   Investors may have gotten some more fuel for their blue-chip
shopping spree.
</P>
<P>
   Better-than-expected earnings reports have been released from
Coke, Caterpillar and Johnson &AMP; Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   All three stocks reside in the blue-chip sector of the market,
which had the hot hand in Monday's advance.
</P>
<P>
   But analysts say it remains to be seen whether investors will
begin to shift new money into some of the mid-level and smaller
companies following the terrible beating they suffered last week.
</P>
</TEXT>
