<HEADLINE> Police Arrest Second Mexico Suspect  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Police have arrested a second suspect in the
killing of five farmers this month in the southern state of
Chiapas, the government news agency Notimex reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Antonio Aguilar Lopez was arrested during a police raid Sunday
evening in the city of Comitan, near the Guatemalan border, Notimex
reported. Last week, police arrested another suspect, Hector
Velasco Gomez, in the area.
</P>
<P>
   Masked gunmen ambushed a group of peasants delivering government
aid April 7, killing five and wounding two others near the mountain
community of Zaragoza.
</P>
<P>
   The seven peasants were attacked and robbed after picking up
more than $21,000 worth of aid intended for agricultural projects
in the area.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, Mexican authorities asked Guatemala for help in
capturing the gunmen who they believed had fled across the border.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said the killings are not related to the region's
Zapatista insurgency.The Zapatistas staged a brief uprising in 1994
in the name of Indian rights and greater democracy. Peace talks
have been stalled for four years.
</P>
</TEXT>
