<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Tuesday, April 18, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nasdaq Gains 190; Dow Up 102
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks continued to gain momentum after last
week's selloff, but most analysts are saying it's too soon to
declare a full recovery. Just before 3 p.m. EDT, the Nasdaq was up
190.69 at 3,729.85. The Dow industrials were up 102.07 ay
10,684.58. On the NYSE, advancers led decliners 1,768-1,158.
Earnings reports provided a catalyst for buying today. Dow
component Johnson &AMP; Johnson reported first-quarter profits beat
analysts' expectations, and Morgan Stanley Dean Witter raised its
rating on Intel, which reports earnings after 4 p.m., to ''strong
buy.''
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 3 p.m. EDT:
