<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberace Piano To Be Auctioned  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- A player piano custom built for Liberace is to be
auctioned May 13.
</P>
<P>
   The 30-year-old, off-white wooden piano was expected to fetch
more than $100,000, said Sloan's Auctions in Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   The player piano, which is also a fully functioning piano, was
bought at a 1988 California estate sale by a collector who lives in
Coral Springs, Fla. It is one of seven pianos made for Liberace,
who died in 1987.
</P>
<P>
   According to the entertainer's sister, this piano was his
favorite, said Albert Parker, vice president in Sloan's Miami
office.
</P>
<P>
   The famed pianist had the instrument built for entertaining
guests at his Las Vegas home. Liberace also recorded his own
arrangements on the piano to create 45 player piano rolls, Parker
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
