<HEADLINE> Diallo Parents Sue NYC for $61M  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The parents of Amadou Diallo on Tuesday sued the
city and the four policemen involved in their son's shooting death
for $61 million -- including $1 million for each of the 41 bullets
fired.
</P>
<P>
   The remaining $20 million was for pain and suffering endured
since the Feb. 4, 1999 killing of their son. Nineteen of the 41
shots struck the unarmed Diallo.
</P>
<P>
   The suit was filed by Diallo's mother, Kadiatou, and his father,
Saikou.
</P>
<P>
   Diallo, a West African immigrant, was shot as he stood in the
vestibule of his Bronx apartment building. The four white officers
in the Street Crime Unit testified at their jury trial they mistook
the wallet Diallo pulled out of his pocket for a gun.
</P>
<P>
   All four officers were acquitted of murder charges in February.
</P>
<P>
   The suit said that the four ''intentionally, wantonly,
recklessly and maliciously'' opened fired.
</P>
<P>
   It also claimed the shooting resulted from aggressive racial
profiling practices sanctioned by police.
</P>
<P>
   The city's corporation counsel did not immediately return calls
for comment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
