<HEADLINE> Court Upholds Job Spanking Award  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WAUSAU, Wis. (AP) -- A former computer analyst who said he was
spanked by his boss in a workplace initiation is entitled to
$143,000 in damages from the company, a state appeals court ruled
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Franklin Smith, 36, said he was whacked at least twice with a
4-foot carpenter's level by Kurt Getschow, president of Phillips
Getschow Co., in 1995 as other workers watched. Getschow, laughing,
then allegeldy put his arm around Smith and said, ''Now you're one
of us.''
</P>
<P>
   Getschow denied spanking Smith.
</P>
<P>
   A jury awarded Smith and his wife $1 million, but the judge
found that amount excessive and reduced it. Wisconsin's 3rd
District Court of Appeals upheld that decision.
</P>
</TEXT>
