<HEADLINE> Salmon Pate Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- An Oregon food company is recalling packages
of its smoked salmon pate because they contain egg yolk without
listing it as an ingredient. People with allergies to eggs could
have serious reactions to the product.
</P>
<P>
   The Dundee-based Northwest Gourmet decided to recall the pate
after it was discovered the egg yolk was not listed. No illnesses
have been reported, the company said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Smoked Salmon Pate comes in a 3.5 ounce gold foil package
inside a box marked with lot numbers 2561006 through 2561130,
110499 and 120499.
</P>
<P>
   The pate was sold in retail stores nationwide and in airports in
Detroit; Dallas/Fort Worth; Portland, Ore.; and Dulles
International in suburban Washington.
</P>
<P>
   The company advises consumers who bought the product to return
it to where it was purchased for a full refund. Consumers with
questions can contact the company at 1-503-554-9060.
</P>
</TEXT>
