<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuggets 105, Jazz 104, OT  </HEADLINE>
By AARON J. LOPEZ, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Raef LaFrentz scored a career-high 32 points and
George McCloud hit a 20-foot jump shot with 25 seconds left in
overtime to lift the Denver Nuggets to a 105-104 victory over the
Utah Jazz on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   LaFrentz also had 17 rebounds and Nick Van Exel added 15 points
and 10 assists for the Nuggets, who struggled to win even though
the Jazz played its reserves for the game's final 19 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Having clinched the Midwest Division in Phoenix on Sunday, Utah
coach Jerry Sloan took the opportunity to rest starters Karl
Malone, John Stockton, Jeff Hornacek, Byron Russell and Olden
Polynice.
</P>
<P>
   Malone finished with 10 points in only 18 minutes, while Utah
was led by Scott Padgett's 13 points. Jacque Vaughn and Armen
Gilliam each scored 12 as the Jazz reserves accounted for 67
points.
</P>
<P>
   After McCloud's go-ahead jump shot, the Jazz missed several
chances to win on the ensuing possession. Quincy Lewis, who hit two
3-pointers in overtime, missed a 3-point attempt and was blocked by
LaFrentz inside the lane.
</P>
<P>
   Utah called a timeout with five seconds left, but threw away the
inbounds pass. James Posey recovered the loose ball and Denver was
able to run out the clock.
</P>
<P>
   LaFrentz gave Denver a two-point lead on a two-handed dunk with
31 seconds left in regulation, but Vaughn -- LaFrentz former college
teammate at Kansas -- tied the game on two free throws seven seconds
later.
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets had two good chances to win it in regulation, but
LaFrentz missed a tough 10-foot shot, and his putback attempt
rolled off the rim as time expired.
</P>
<P>
   Though neither team had anything at stake, things got a little
chippy in the third quarter as Van Exel took exception when
Stockton hit him after the whistle.
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel yelled at Polynice seconds later after being fouled by
the Utah center, and Malone picked up an offensive foul when he
knocked Van Exel down with a hard screen.
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets, behind the outside shooting of LaFrentz, shook off
the physical play and led 77-74 heading into the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Malone had three assists and joined Kareem Abdul-Jabbar,
Wilt Chamberlain and Charles Barkley as the only players in NBA
history with 20,000 points, 10,000 rebounds and 4,000 assists. ...
In their first season at the Pepsi Center, the Nuggets won 25 home
games, the most since the 1993-94 team won 28 games. ... Hornacek
was 3-for-3 from the foul line to raise his NBA-leading free-throw
percentage to 94.9, which would rank third-best in league history.
... Denver's backups had 25 points after scoring 18 in the previous
two games combined.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
